<h2>
    Popular Fishing Techniques in Local Waters
</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Still Fishing with Bait</strong>: Great for trout and panfish—use worms, PowerBait, or salmon eggs.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Lure Fishing</strong>: Spinners (like Rooster Tails), jigs, and soft plastics work well for bass and trout.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Fly Fishing</strong>: Less common in urban areas, but effective in clear creeks and rivers nearby.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Kayak Fishing</strong>: Ideal for Tualatin River and some quiet pond edges.
    </li>
</ul>
